HEADWORD: Precocity
<hw>Pre*coc"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧cocit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of
being precocious; untimely ripeness; premature development, especially
of the mental powers; forwardness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Saucy <qex>precociousness</qex> in learning.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Mannyngham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>precocity</qex> which sometimes distinguishes uncommon
genius.</q> <rj><qau>Wirt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precoetanean</ent>⟦br⟧
